        "content": "<p>I think you would also have an easier time working with <code>2*n</code> for any <code>n</code> instead of assuming you have an even <code>n</code>. This way you don't have to worry about division.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">GroupTheory</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Subgroup</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Centralizer</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">GroupTheory</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">SpecificGroups</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Dihedral</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CentralSymmetryGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Subgroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">DihedralGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exercise2_2_7b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Subgroup</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">center</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">DihedralGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">CentralSymmetryGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
